1
00:01:02,149 --> 00:01:06,769
[Episode 1]

2
00:01:18,425 --> 00:01:20,505
Mom, look!

3
00:01:21,340 --> 00:01:23,033
Do you know what my dream is?

4
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:27,790
I want to live in a house and
have a dog like this when I grow up.

5
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:29,749
Why are you alone?

6
00:01:29,749 --> 00:01:30,884
Huh?

7
00:01:30,884 --> 00:01:33,628
Why don't you draw the person
you're going to marry?

8
00:01:33,628 --> 00:01:37,468
And maybe you can make the house bigger.

9
00:01:38,487 --> 00:01:45,230
Remember, Maika, a woman's happiness
is decided by her marriage.

10
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:47,628
You will be unhappy
if you take longer to get married.

11
00:01:47,628 --> 00:01:49,967
So, find a good person while in your twenties.

12
00:01:49,967 --> 00:01:53,026
You absolutely must not let him get away.

13
00:01:53,026 --> 00:02:01,218
I met your dad in my twenties
and I truly felt happy when you were born.

14
00:02:01,218 --> 00:02:03,506
It really was for the best.

15
00:02:05,352 --> 00:02:09,640
I remembered the things my mother
would often say to me since I was a child,

16
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:12,474
every step of the way.

17
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,269
[BirdLeft]

18
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:35,985
I met my first boyfriend
on my twentieth birthday.

19
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:38,198
And then...

20
00:02:38,198 --> 00:02:41,448
Good morning, Maika.

21
00:02:41,448 --> 00:02:43,421
Good morning.

22
00:02:45,489 --> 00:02:48,468
Are you sure about staying in tonight?

23
00:02:49,330 --> 00:02:53,638
Yeah, I want to spend some relaxing time.

24
00:02:53,638 --> 00:02:55,224
Got it.

25
00:02:57,481 --> 00:03:04,609
Today is our third anniversary, and I'm
expecting a proposal from Narimitsu tonight.

26
00:03:19,121 --> 00:03:21,754
What do you want to eat tonight?

27
00:03:21,754 --> 00:03:23,771
Why don't you decide?

28
00:03:23,771 --> 00:03:26,256
Only if it isn't too much trouble.

29
00:03:28,645 --> 00:03:30,292
Okay!

30
00:03:32,972 --> 00:03:34,806
Maika!

31
00:03:35,551 --> 00:03:37,846
Have you been tired recently?

32
00:03:37,846 --> 00:03:39,966
Why do you ask?

33
00:03:39,966 --> 00:03:45,749
Your skin seems pale. The moisture...
It seems like your skin is missing moisture.

34
00:03:45,749 --> 00:03:48,645
Really, no way!

35
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,982
Does it look rough?

36
00:03:51,982 --> 00:03:55,661
What should I do? It's a special day.

37
00:03:55,661 --> 00:03:57,540
A special day?

38
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:02,038
It's not exactly special,
but it's more like a little anniversary.

39
00:04:02,038 --> 00:04:04,419
An anniversary? What kind of anniversary?

40
00:04:04,419 --> 00:04:09,020
I'm really curious! Please tell me!

41
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:10,873
Well, break time is over.

42
00:04:10,873 --> 00:04:13,014
Let's push through the rest.

43
00:04:14,789 --> 00:04:16,601
Huh?

44
00:04:22,609 --> 00:04:24,866
Let me guess. Beef stew?

45
00:04:24,866 --> 00:04:27,126
- Yeah.
- Wow, I'm really excited.

46
00:04:27,126 --> 00:04:29,347
That's my favorite.

47
00:04:29,347 --> 00:04:31,464
Of course, it's our anniversary.

48
00:04:31,464 --> 00:04:33,832
It'll take a bit longer to simmer.

49
00:04:33,832 --> 00:04:35,870
That's fine.

50
00:04:40,952 --> 00:04:43,067
Aren't you going to answer it?

51
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:46,422
Nope, weird solicitations keep coming.

52
00:04:50,561 --> 00:04:53,591
We've been together for three years already.

53
00:04:53,591 --> 00:04:55,479
Time flies, doesn't it?

54
00:04:55,479 --> 00:04:57,046
Yeah.

55
00:04:57,710 --> 00:04:59,063
Narimitsu.

56
00:04:59,063 --> 00:05:00,603
Yeah?

57
00:05:01,442 --> 00:05:07,523
When we just started dating,
do you remember what you said?

58
00:05:07,523 --> 00:05:10,279
Huh? What did I say?

59
00:05:11,906 --> 00:05:19,266
You said we'd think about getting married
after around three years of dating.

60
00:05:19,266 --> 00:05:22,417
Oh, did I say that?

61
00:05:23,271 --> 00:05:26,534
- Yeah, we...
- Ah!

62
00:05:26,534 --> 00:05:29,757
I forgot to buy wine. I'll go get some.

63
00:05:32,711 --> 00:05:34,304
Okay.

64
00:05:55,345 --> 00:05:56,730
Oh.

65
00:05:58,020 --> 00:06:00,740
I forgot the whipped cream.

66
00:06:06,408 --> 00:06:08,483
[Narimitsu Matoba]

67
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:37,075
Narimitsu.

68
00:06:52,423 --> 00:06:55,383
Why can't we go to your house?

69
00:06:55,383 --> 00:06:57,970
Maika is there today.

70
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:03,351
Then maybe I'll just wait until Maika leaves.

71
00:07:04,326 --> 00:07:07,499
- Not today.
- Why not?

72
00:07:07,499 --> 00:07:09,454
Today is not a good day.

73
00:07:09,454 --> 00:07:12,109
I'll wait until she leaves.

74
00:07:13,586 --> 00:07:15,696
No. No.

75
00:07:16,903 --> 00:07:19,409
I'll wait anyway.

76
00:07:24,538 --> 00:07:27,809
You see, if I'm late getting home,
Maika will get suspicious.

77
00:07:27,809 --> 00:07:30,728
Then I'll answer it. Hand it over.

78
00:07:30,728 --> 00:07:33,539
Seriously, stop it.
She hasn't found out about us yet.

79
00:07:33,539 --> 00:07:38,830
But you said that you'd break up with her.

80
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:41,509
You haven't kept your promise.

81
00:07:41,509 --> 00:07:43,388
I'm just waiting for the right time.

82
00:07:43,388 --> 00:07:45,325
We work at the same place.

83
00:07:45,325 --> 00:07:49,658
But that goes for me too, you know?

84
00:07:49,658 --> 00:07:52,688
Yeah, you're right, but...

85
00:07:52,688 --> 00:07:54,094
Don't worry.

86
00:07:55,272 --> 00:07:58,618
Maika is almost 30, so she's anxious.

87
00:07:58,618 --> 00:08:02,224
Maybe she thinks she'll have
no chance in love if she loses me.

88
00:08:02,224 --> 00:08:05,326
Honestly, I don't know about those things.

89
00:08:05,326 --> 00:08:08,541
I'll make it up to you next time, okay?

90
00:08:23,975 --> 00:08:27,276
Sorry, I'm late.

91
00:08:27,276 --> 00:08:29,728
Hey, are you leaving already?

92
00:08:31,147 --> 00:08:33,651
- I bought something really nice.
- What's going on here?

93
00:08:33,651 --> 00:08:35,159
Huh?

94
00:08:38,229 --> 00:08:40,118
What's wrong?

95
00:08:41,188 --> 00:08:43,325
It's too late to ask that question.

96
00:08:49,306 --> 00:08:52,043
What do you mean by the right time to break up?

97
00:10:05,902 --> 00:10:07,453
I look like a ghost.

98
00:10:11,536 --> 00:10:14,143
Good morning.

99
00:10:14,143 --> 00:10:15,303
Good morning.

100
00:10:15,303 --> 00:10:16,461
Did you hear about it?

101
00:10:16,461 --> 00:10:20,589
The new president will be greeting us
at the morning meeting.

102
00:10:21,265 --> 00:10:22,720
Oh, is it?

103
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:26,053
You know, the handsome son of the chairman.

104
00:10:35,145 --> 00:10:37,022
Not interested at all?

105
00:10:38,161 --> 00:10:40,392
[Corporate Philosophy]

106
00:10:59,698 --> 00:11:01,338
Oh, here he comes.

107
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:44,253
Well then, let's hear from our new president.

108
00:11:46,244 --> 00:11:50,698
Starting today, I'll be the president of BirdLeft.

109
00:11:50,698 --> 00:11:52,958
I'm Shun Satori.

110
00:11:53,544 --> 00:11:56,552
He's even more handsome than the rumors said.

111
00:11:56,552 --> 00:11:59,155
My aim is to create a company
with a comfortable work environment.

112
00:11:59,155 --> 00:12:01,647
So, I would appreciate everyone's support.

113
00:12:17,330 --> 00:12:18,873
President.

114
00:12:23,303 --> 00:12:25,920
I hope to receive your cooperation.

115
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:28,133
Thank you.

116
00:12:54,163 --> 00:12:56,452
Maika Hattori.

117
00:13:06,409 --> 00:13:10,279
- Mr. Akiyama, about tomorrow's meeting...
- President.

118
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,653
I have reiterated it several times.

119
00:13:12,653 --> 00:13:15,895
There's no need to be so formal with me.

120
00:13:15,895 --> 00:13:18,183
You're the company's president.

121
00:13:19,076 --> 00:13:20,923
Ah.

122
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:23,883
That's right.

123
00:13:23,883 --> 00:13:26,942
It's really hard to break a habit
of so many years.

124
00:13:29,682 --> 00:13:34,569
When I first met you, I was in high school.

125
00:13:34,569 --> 00:13:36,642
It's been 12 years already.

126
00:13:36,642 --> 00:13:38,286
Yes.

127
00:13:46,868 --> 00:13:48,503
Akiyama.

128
00:13:50,608 --> 00:13:52,175
Yes.

129
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,967
I need you to look into something later.

130
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:57,847
It's personal.

131
00:14:00,545 --> 00:14:02,143
Sure.

132
00:14:18,358 --> 00:14:20,931
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

133
00:14:20,931 --> 00:14:26,124
I'm still as busy as ever,
but it definitely boosts my motivation.

134
00:14:26,761 --> 00:14:28,873
Majima, you so straightforward.

135
00:14:28,873 --> 00:14:30,342
Of course.

136
00:14:30,342 --> 00:14:34,161
The effect of a young handsome president
is enormous.

137
00:14:34,161 --> 00:14:36,213
- I totally get it.
- Did you see his face?

138
00:14:36,213 --> 00:14:38,513
- I did. He looks really young.
- He does, right?

139
00:14:38,513 --> 00:14:41,656
- Taller than me.
- I'd love to date him.

140
00:14:41,656 --> 00:14:44,518
- Let's work hard for that.
- Okay.

141
00:14:47,889 --> 00:14:49,903
Not here, you always do it.

142
00:14:49,903 --> 00:14:54,219
So, you see, at home, right? Not at work.

143
00:14:54,219 --> 00:14:56,277
It's fine. No one will notice.

144
00:14:56,277 --> 00:15:00,868
- Jeez...
- Just a hug, just once.

145
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:05,520
Hey, give me another hug.

146
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:07,205
It's not good to do that at work.

147
00:15:07,205 --> 00:15:09,018
Why not?

148
00:15:09,714 --> 00:15:13,914
Oh, fine, whatever.

149
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:16,246
You're so sticky today.

150
00:15:19,697 --> 00:15:21,702
Why am I running away?

151
00:15:22,656 --> 00:15:25,529
I haven't done anything wrong.

152
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,198
Narimitsu.

153
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:42,173
I want to have a proper conversation.

154
00:15:42,173 --> 00:15:45,185
Please stop ambushing me like this.

155
00:15:45,185 --> 00:15:47,050
I didn't say anything yesterday.

156
00:15:47,050 --> 00:15:49,390
Hey, wait.

157
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:52,193
You said you were considering marrying me, right?

158
00:15:52,193 --> 00:15:55,048
What's your relationship with Hayashida?

159
00:16:05,224 --> 00:16:08,291
You found out.
So, I don't need to hide anymore.

160
00:16:09,858 --> 00:16:15,151
- What does that even mean?
- You're so annoying.

161
00:16:17,329 --> 00:16:19,030
Let's just break up.

162
00:16:21,076 --> 00:16:24,786
Just come pick up your stuff whenever.

163
00:16:37,556 --> 00:16:41,261
So, are you coming back
for the memorial service next month?

164
00:16:43,498 --> 00:16:45,458
I'm busy.

165
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:48,155
I can't say for sure yet.

166
00:16:48,155 --> 00:16:51,390
Okay. Let me know early
if you decide to come back.

167
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:53,698
We have preparations to make here.

168
00:16:53,698 --> 00:16:55,884
Is Narimitsu coming along?

169
00:16:55,884 --> 00:16:58,366
You've been together for three years, right?

170
00:16:58,366 --> 00:17:01,020
Hasn't the topic of marriage come up?

171
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:05,757
It's better to find someone more stable,
but there's no one willing to marry you.

172
00:17:05,757 --> 00:17:08,609
It's the only alternative. What can we do?

173
00:17:08,609 --> 00:17:11,374
You need to decide before you turn 30.

174
00:17:23,094 --> 00:17:27,348
Wow. He's so cool.

175
00:17:43,624 --> 00:17:45,283
President.

176
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:10,600
Hi there.

177
00:18:11,439 --> 00:18:15,088
By the way, thanks for the beef stew.

178
00:18:15,996 --> 00:18:17,826
It was delicious.

179
00:18:17,826 --> 00:18:20,865
There was also plenty of meat.

180
00:18:20,865 --> 00:18:24,647
But perhaps you should've simmered it a bit more.

181
00:18:24,647 --> 00:18:29,828
The meat was hard, and it was a little bland.

182
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:36,604
- You...
- But it was the first time

183
00:18:36,604 --> 00:18:41,279
I had home-cooked food in that house,
so it was refreshing.

184
00:18:41,279 --> 00:18:47,261
I can't cook, so I always eat out, you know.

185
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:56,604
Huh, what? What's wrong?

186
00:18:56,604 --> 00:19:00,236
Miss Hattori suddenly got angry.

187
00:19:00,236 --> 00:19:04,945
I was just talking about dinner.

188
00:19:14,094 --> 00:19:16,121
Are you okay?

189
00:19:16,121 --> 00:19:18,542
Did something happen?

190
00:19:49,329 --> 00:19:51,449
I'm sorry.

191
00:19:51,449 --> 00:19:53,269
Are you okay?

192
00:19:53,989 --> 00:19:55,854
Yes.

193
00:19:55,854 --> 00:19:57,748
It's nothing.

194
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:01,293
It can't be nothing.

195
00:20:05,452 --> 00:20:07,754
President!

196
00:20:07,754 --> 00:20:09,719
I'm sorry!

197
00:20:17,024 --> 00:20:20,980
Did something happen with that girl from earlier?

198
00:20:23,123 --> 00:20:25,944
Uh, no.

199
00:20:36,973 --> 00:20:41,146
Actually, a colleague of mine...

200
00:20:41,146 --> 00:20:44,045
I didn't know he was two-timing me.

201
00:20:45,178 --> 00:20:48,966
I feel like such a fool.

202
00:20:57,821 --> 00:21:02,855
You don't have to force a smile
when you're hurt.

203
00:21:19,832 --> 00:21:21,336
I'm sorry.

204
00:21:42,752 --> 00:21:44,563
You want revenge?

205
00:21:46,985 --> 00:21:48,358
What?

206
00:21:50,793 --> 00:21:56,513
Pretend to be my girlfriend,
and get revenge on the two of them.

207
00:21:56,513 --> 00:22:01,872
No... Do you want to get back at them?

208
00:22:18,262 --> 00:22:21,225
Fake relationship?

209
00:22:21,986 --> 00:22:27,064
To get back at the guy who cheated on you,
I think I'm perfect for the job.

210
00:22:27,651 --> 00:22:29,442
But...

211
00:22:31,532 --> 00:22:37,366
Of course,
I want cooperation from you in return.

212
00:22:39,718 --> 00:22:42,621
Cooperation?

213
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:56,646
I have a fiancÃ©e chosen by my parents,
and I want to get away from her.

214
00:22:58,302 --> 00:23:04,352
So, I want you to pretend to be my girlfriend,
and I want to call off the engagement.

215
00:23:15,521 --> 00:23:18,340
I'll do whatever I can to help you.

216
00:23:18,340 --> 00:23:20,297
That's reassuring.

217
00:23:21,596 --> 00:23:22,769
What are you doing?

218
00:23:22,769 --> 00:23:25,878
Are you envious because I'm happy?

219
00:23:25,878 --> 00:23:28,557
What do you like about Maika Hattori?

220
00:23:28,557 --> 00:23:31,429
Keep this between us, okay?

221
00:23:31,429 --> 00:23:33,489
Are those two dating?

222
00:23:33,489 --> 00:23:35,089
You're a bad liar.

223
00:23:35,089 --> 00:23:36,542
Aren't we partners?

224
00:23:36,542 --> 00:23:39,100
Is this revenge? Answer me!

225
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:40,360
Just go away right now.

226
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:43,373
I won't allow you to get anywhere
near her anymore.

227
00:23:43,373 --> 00:23:45,184
President?

228
00:23:47,611 --> 00:23:49,878
You're calling me that again.

229
00:23:49,878 --> 00:23:54,319
If you call me President again, I'll kiss you.

230
00:23:55,694 --> 00:23:58,474
Who are you taking revenge on?
